&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Transformation and Planning Co-ordinator&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In order to progress the review and transformation of health care in Morecambe Bay, we wish to recruit to 2.0 WTE new roles on a 12 month fixed term contract/secondment basis.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As part of becoming ready to transform from a Morecambe Bay CCG in to an Integrated Care Partnership with single Clinical Commissioning Group across Lancashire and South Cumbria, we are looking for individuals who are able to help us to progress local transformation of a range of services across both Adult community and Children and Young Peoples services. This will involve collaborative working with service providers to agree service re-design and to refresh Service Specifications as well as monitoring existing services to ensure that the offer to our local population reflects the ambition of Bay Health and Care Partners.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The work will involve leading on delegated service areas, working with partners to review and to modernise and introduce new ways of working – this could include some service user engagement and presentations to groups and committees with appropriate support. Given the challenging timescales and additional pressures of the Covid 19 pandemic, we are looking for candidates who can work as part of a wider team and bring energy and focus at this important time in the NHS&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For an informal conversation, please contact Helen McConville Mob 07970 270446 or e mail&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;helen.mcconville@morecambebayccg.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameHelen McConvilleJob titleSenior ManagerEmail addresshelen.mcconvillle@morecambebayccg.nhs.ukTelephone number07917 270446&lt;/p&gt;
